                <head>273. Summary of Discussion and Conclusions of a Policy Review Committee
                        Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d273fn1">Source: <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJEJ_1">Carter</persName> Library, National Security
                        Council, Institutional Files, Box 63, <gloss target="#t_PRC_1">PRC</gloss>
                        028 7/27/77 North/South Issues [1]. Confidential. The meeting took place in
                        the White House Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1"
                            >Brzezinski</persName> forwarded the summary to <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJEJ_1">Carter</persName> under cover of a July 30
                        memorandum; <persName corresp="#p_CJEJ_1">Carter</persName> initialed
                            <persName corresp="#p_BZK_1">Brzezinski</persName>’s memorandum and
                        indicated his approval of the summary. (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1977-07-27T15:30:00-04:00" to="1977-07-27T17:00:00-04:00">July 27,
                            1977, 3:30–5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>North-South Strategy</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
